  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_8' aria-label=\" M/s Faime Makers Pvt. Ltd. versus District Deputy Registrar, Co-operative Societies(3), Mumbai & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('8','2025','2025_5_331_341','2025INSC423'); ><font size='4'> <strong>M/S FAIME MAKERS PVT. LTD.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>DISTRICT DEPUTY REGISTRAR, CO-OPERATIVE SOCIETIES(3), MUMBAI & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 331</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 423</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001622025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASANNA BHALACHANDRA VARALE</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The appellant&rsquo;s writ petition, assailing the correctness of the order dated 05.10.2021 passed by the District Deputy Registrar, Co-operative Societies, Mumbai/Competent Authority, was dismissed by the of Flats (Regulation of the Promotion of Construction, Sale, Management and Transfer) Act, 1963 &ndash; ss.5, 11 &ndash; The respondent No.2-Society applied for a Unilateral Certificate of Deemed Conveyance &ndash; By an order dated 22.02.2021, the Competent Authority dismissed the respondent<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 31-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 4650/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('8','2025','2025_5_331_341','2025INSC423','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'>